{"ts":"2026-06-26T08:21:45.040Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"xeakljjb","input":{"summary":"### Investigation & Execution Summary\n\nWe conducted a high-precision, premium mobile responsive polish pass across key interface boundaries in GFF AI without modifying the approved landing page or introducing slug routes or backend connections.\n\n#### Key Enhancements Made:\n1. **Global Header (`components/Header.tsx`):**\n   - Implemented a maximum viewport height constraint (`max-h-[90vh]`) and native overflow scroll (`overflow-y-auto`) on the mobile navigation drawer. This ensures all 10 strategic navigation pages and CTAs are fully scrollable and perfectly reachable on shorter mobile screen heights.\n\n2. **Platform Console & Product Previews (`components/inner-pages/PlatformProductPreview.tsx`):**\n   - Refactored the vertical console sidebar menu into an Apple/Vercel-style, premium, horizontally-scrolling tab list on mobile screens (`flex-row md:flex-col overflow-x-auto whitespace-nowrap`).\n   - Integrated dynamic design-system borders: active indicators animate cleanly horizontally under the active tab on mobile devices, and switch back to vertical sidebars on desktop viewports (`border-b-2 md:border-b-0 md:border-l-2`).\n\n3. **Secure Client Workspace & Tables (`components/portal/ClientWorkspace.tsx`):**\n   - Wrapped all high-density informational tables (Projects, Invoices, eBPF Telemetry Analytics, and Active AI Operations) inside responsive scroll containers (`overflow-x-auto min-w-[500px]`). This avoids truncation or layout breaking on narrow screen widths.\n   - Refactored list items in Strategic Programs, Secure Documents, and active Human-in-the-Loop Approvals from strict inline flex alignments into adaptive stacking blocks (`flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4`). This results in balanced typography, excellent vertical rhythm, and highly polished mobile layouts.\n\n4. **Interactive SVG Architectural Diagrams:**\n   - Standardized SVG width/height styling to scale continuously utilizing proportional aspect ratios (`h-auto aspect-[...]`), avoiding layout boundaries overflow.\n\n#### Verification & QA Results:\n- Ran focused file checks and global linter checks (`npx eslint`), returning **100% clean** results with no warnings or errors.\n- Checked global type safety using `npx tsc --noEmit` and confirmed there are **no type errors or compilation constraints**.\n- Confirmed that the landing page was kept intact and untouched, and no prohibited patterns (such as fake dashboards or database hooks) were created.","verified":true}}}
